notesStmt.note: Paper: Syro-Egyptian handmade paper, chain lines in groups of three occasionally visible.

msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Collection of biographies drawn chiefly from the Ṭabaqāt al-Shāfiʻīyah of Tāj al-Dīn al-Subkī. The leaves are disbound and have considerable gaps and lacunae. One leaf contains material from al-Ghazzālī's al-Wasīṭ fī al-madhhab.

author.persName: Subkī, Tāj al-Dīn ʻAbd al-Wahhāb ibn ʻAlī, approximately 1327-1370
سبكي، تاج الدين عبد الوهاب بن علي،

respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 19 long lines; short titles in upper left recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a large and clear naskh.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubrications in red including marginal comments.

origin.p: Item is not dated, possibly produced in the 14th or 15th century based on the paper..

history.provenance: Gift of John Frederick Lewis to the Library of the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning
